4 HR____ CELEBRATING THE LIFE OF JOE FRANK KNIGHT, JR.
5
6 WHEREAS, it is with profound sorrow that we note the
7 death of Joe Frank Knight, Jr. of Montgomery, Alabama, on
8 February 17, 2025, at the age of 60; and
9 WHEREAS, his departure leaves a void in the lives of
10 his loving family, many friends, and the community where he
11 was highly regarded; and
12 WHEREAS, Mr. Knight was born on November 9, 1964, to
13 the dearly departed Joe Frank Knight, Sr. and Lee Ella Owens
14 in Sellers, Alabama; he attended Montgomery County High
15 School in Ramer, Alabama; he was a dedicated employee at
16 Wade and Gravel for more than 20 years until his health
17 declined; and
18 WHEREAS, Mr. Knight enjoyed the outdoors and would go
19 fishing at every opportunity; he was an avid fan of football
20 and drag racing, watching both as time permitted; he was a
21 loving father and grandfather; his son Jamal, having learned
22 from his father the value of hard work, opened his own
23 businesses in his father's honor, The Wash Wizard and Wizard
24 Enterprise, in Montgomery; and
25 WHEREAS, he leaves to cherish his memory two sons,
26 Darren Knight (Gabrielle) and Jamal Knight; bonus daughter,
27 Shiamber Pierce (Renaldo); grandchildren, Aniya, Mahogany,
28 Noah, Braxton, and Ariyunah; bonus grandchildren, Raegan,
Page 1

Noah, Braxton, and Ariyunah; bonus grandchildren, Raegan,
HR73 INTRODUCED
29 Taylor, Ta'Shun, and Za'laiyah; siblings, Elaine Wright,
30 Joyce Taylor, Mary Ann Knight, Marvin Taylor, Sidney Owens
31 (Karen), Lexie Owens, and Cherry Owens; and a host of nieces
32 nephews, cousins, friends, and his very special friend,
33 Tameka Pettway; and
34 WHEREAS, although his presence will be greatly
35 missed, the memory of Joe Knight will be cherished in the
36 hearts of all who knew and loved him; now therefore,
37 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
38 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That the death of Joe Frank Knight,
39 Jr. is recorded with deep sadness, and even as we mourn his
40 death and the loss it represents, we also celebrate his
41 life; this resolution is offered in highest tribute, along
42 with heartfelt sympathy to his family, whose grief is shared
43 by many.
